title: Great heat protection, somewhat difficult to clean
text:
I ordered this silicone pad to place on my vanity so that I could rest my curling/straightening irons on it while getting ready without having to worry about scorching the wood vanity top. Overall, it works well and it just small enough to squeeze between the two drawers that come up on either side of my vanity. I have a love/hate feeling for the little raised "dots" that cover each side of the mat. I like them because they raise the hot tool when resting on the mat to give extra heat protection to my vanity top underneath it. However, I also put my makeup on at my vanity and because of the silicone surface, every little drop of makeup powder is attracted to and clings to the silicone mat surface. The silicone isn't that difficult to clean (I use either pledge spray or a lysol wipe), but the little raised dots make it difficult to get into all the little grooves in order to get the mat perfectly clean. I could move the mat while I put my makeup on, but I don't have many places to put it on where I get ready, so this would be a huge inconvenience. Plus, regardless of where i put the mat, it will still collect dust overtime and have the same cleaning issue.
As a solution to cleaning the mat, I started running it under warm water and using a dish brush with bristles to scrub the mat and get in those difficult grooves, which has been successful as far as perfectly cleaning the mat - it's just a little more tedious than I'd like it to be.

title: A good product at a good price.
text:
.

This Radiance eye cream is a super moisturizer that works well as an overall facial moisturizer, which is how I use it. It goes on and absorbs well, and it's not oily, which makes it great for putting on under makeup.

The hyaluronic acid, aloe vera, and retinol really brighten up the skin and smooth out those pesky little crow's feet.

For 1.8 ounces (which comes, by the way, in one of those handy push-down dispensers that you can do with one finger), the price is competitive with those at big box stores.

This eye cream is manufactured according to cGMP (current Good Manufacturing Practices) guidelines, which is important to me. The FDA neither reviews nor approves cosmetics products, and the cGMP seal assures that basic manufacturing practices have been met. Also,a cGMP label means that the facility is registered with the FDA.

I like this product, and I can highly recommend it.

title: Cute MOM gift but not as fragrant or impressive as I expected
text:
[[VIDEOID:f77804a8088c40dfbef6fdcfacf8b15a]] There are three individually wrapped bath bombs in this set along with one bar of hand soap and a package of dried rose petals. In total there are five items. The bath bombs spell MOM with the heart substituting for the letter O.

The outside packaging looks giftable but the inside is just an ordinary uninspiring throw-away box. The fragrance of the bombs and soap is hardly noticeable. It has a whisper of rose aroma and I detect no lavender at all. I did try the letter M bomb in a hand bath and it dissolved in 5 minutes in lukewarm water and a nice foam of suds lasted about 10 minutes. The results initially felt moisturizing because my hands felt a little oily after the hand bath; however, eventually I needed to moisturize my hands with lotion.

With regard to the dried petals, one has to like something like that in their bath because it requires straining the water so that they don't go down the drain. For me, I would never use petals in a bath, so keep the recipient in mind when ordering this.

The bar of soap is the only item that would be used by most people.

One thing I love is that the color of the dissolved bomb did not adhere to my skin, my hand bath, or my towel. That is not always the case with bath bombs today.

The current price of $9.74 ($12.99 minus 25%) comes to $1.95 per item which is reasonable.

title: Nice electric shaver by Wahl
text:
I had a set of Wahl clippers that lasted for over a decade. I finally got a new pair of clippers and through the old clippers away. I miss my old Wahl clippers they were a super workhorse set of clippers. I had no idea that Wahl even made shavers.

I have had quite a few high-end electric shavers, and they all have the same problem, they just don't shave as close as a razor. The positive thing about electric shavers is that they are easy to use for quick touch ups and convenient shaves when you don't want to mess with water and creams and lotions.

This Wahl shaver, in particular, is pretty nice. It shaves about as close as other electric shavers, which isn't as close as a manual razor, but with repeated use and going back and forth, it is better than no shave. Some type of pre-shave lotion, like Williams Lectric shave, helps a little.

Still, this is a pretty decent shaver. It charges fast and holds the charge for a long time. The top pops off easy to clean the blades. You can use the provided brush or just rinse it off with water. You can also use it in the shower or wet/dry shave. The directions say not to submerge it under 3 feet of water.

It also has a shaver that pops up for sideburns or whatever you would want a clean smooth line on. Bottom line this is a pretty good shaver.

title: Why this is a good value...
text:
This is pure genius.
After unscrewing the top of the cap, you'll see the film that protects the batteries. After you remove it, put the top back on and separate the light unit from the jar.
The red LED light will be activated by pressing against your skin. Does that light actually do anything, or is it a gimmick?
There are a number of high-priced red light units on the market. They were first used in dermatologist offices and med spas. When they first came out, I had a red Tanda unit. This is exactly the same concept, and yes, you will have a slight difference.
The amount of cream gone in the jar has been for about 10 applications. I do it at night so I can relax while holding the unit at various places on my face. The red light goes on when you press slightly on the metal ring, as you can see in the photographs. As you press it to the area of your face that you want treated, slide it from the middle of your face outward, for 3 minutes. Then go to the next area. This way you get a little bit of a lymphatic massage. If you suffer with sinus headaches, this action is very good at offering some relief.
The cream is very lightly fragranced with a fresh scent. It's a gel or mousse type of cream.
After purchasing this, you can get the cream refill.

So much cheaper than buying an LED light device like a Tanda.

title: light, floral lavender
text:
Lavender is my #1 go-to essential oil. I think I use it in 90% of my blends, whether in the diffuser or in topical blends (or sprays, etc). The only thing I definitely don‚Äôt use it for is my home-made cleaning products where citrus oils are the only essential oils.

This particular oil is a very delicate scent ‚Äì some lavender oils can pack quite a punch in terms of the scent. This is certainly floral and has a ‚Äòhigh note‚Äô to it. You can easily pick it out of a blend. It‚Äôs my first oil from New York Biology and I‚Äôm very pleased.

I love blending lavender in particular with chamomile, as it has an almost instantaneous calming effect. Also love to blend it with bergamot, ylang ylang, mandarin, and a drop of lime.

The bottle is very large, a dark brown color to protect the oil from UV rays which can damage the oils and decrease the shelf life. My favorite way to dispense oils is with the eye dropper (the euro droppers found in smaller bottles tend to gush several drops at once, so that‚Äôs definitely not my preference) ‚Äì you can really control how many drops you dispense with these eye droppers.

Arrived well protected in bubble wrap and there was no leaks.

* I received the oil for evaluation and review

title: Straight razor with a "guard"
text: That's basically what this is.  First off, the box is written in Chinese, I believe, with absolutely no English on it.  No instructions other than a pair of pictures.  Not great pictures either.  Not to be deterred, I opened the box, pulled one of the razors from the box, removed the plastic cover and tried it.  If you look closely at the one picture, you will see what appears to be a drop of blood - it is.  That is why I described this as a straight razor with a guard in quotes.  Make NO mistake, these are SHARP.  Use them delicately and only on smooth skin.  If you have a blemish, a mole or anything just slightly raised on your skin, it will be cut off.  You will bleed.  Just want others to be aware of what this is and to take care not to hurt themselves.

title: Fantastic natural-looking STAY PUT color with excellent pencil shape for easy application
text: Okay, I am a fan but with caveats. I love the long chiseled pencil shape because it makes it easier to apply straight stokes of color to my very thin brows without looking drawn on or penciled in. However, it does skip a bit compared to my gel brow color that is applied with a brush. The sponge tip is great for softening the sharp line on the thicker area of my brow and i dab it with a bit of eye shadow to set it.  The color stays put and looks natural without leaning towards red. What more can you ask of a good brow pencil for brunettes? I overplucked my brows in my youth when pencil-thin brows were was the style (okay, I'm dating myself here) but this seems to apply quickly and easily and works well with super-thin brows without making me look like Groucho Marx. It works, it stays and looks great. Gals with thicker brows will reap the most benefit b using the mascara type brush for the most natural look and pigment distribution.

title: Test of time: Aced!
text:
According to my Amazon's purchase records, I bought this shaver back in June 2008 and I've used it almost exclusively up until recently when it was replaced by a [[ASIN:B000PKNPES Philips Norelco arcitec 1050 Men's Shaver]] not because it stopped working but because the Arcitec was on sale for a price where it made more sense to buy a brand-new shaver than to replace the old SpeedXL's shaving heads. As of now, the SpeedXL is still in perfect working order and it's likely to be one of my kids first shavers when they are going to need a first shaver (soon).

I am writing this only to testify to the quality of this product. I had no problems with it whatsoever, it never let me down, the battery still holds enough charge for maybe half a dozen shaves, runs as silently as on day one and it's a near-zero maintenance item, requiring nothing beyond the heads cleaning after each shave by placing them under the faucet. The one issue I had was that the skin on my neck got irritated from time to time but it was never anything major that wouldn't go away after a few hours.

Si, it's goodbye to the SpeedXL for me (hello Arcitec) but it's not this shaver's end of career. It's going to be in service, again, in about a year or two, who knows for how much longer :)

title: I have very thick, curly hair and these hold a lot of hair securely.
text:
I've been using these for a month now on a weekly basis (a few days each week) and I'm happy to report that none of them have broken! I've had some (from other brands) that have broken on me after just a week or two - these have not done that.

They're really great quality and can hold quite a bit of hair. My hair is really thick and tightly curled and I can easily part my hair into just 6 sections and hold each section tightly and securely with these; they're definitely strong and flexible. It's quite refreshing. Sometimes, depending on how I position them, these can be a little too tight actually. They never slip off or budge at all!

Also, these clips do not pull my hair or get tangled. The colors are very nice too. It's a nice change from the all black clips that I have. They can be a little hard to handle when your hands are wet or have products on them - they get a little slippery. Other than that, I have no complaints.

I received this product complimentary in exchange for my honest, unbiased review. All opinions are 100% mine.

title: Amazing.
text:
This is the best mask I have tried so far. The texture is strange, it doesn't have the mud texture, but rather a chocolate gelatin pudding texture.
You just use a thin layer, so you don't need a lot, and the bottle is huge so it will definitely last a while! Then you leave it on for 15 minutes. After having it on for about 10 minutes it started to burn, I could literally feel all of the impurities being sucked out of my pores. It was only a slight burning sensation so I wasn't worried. I have extremely sensitive skin, so I was nervous to see how my skin reacted once I took it off.
I love that it doesn't make a mess in the sink when you take it off like other masks do, it just turned the water a slight grey color.
After taking off the mask, certain areas of my face were red but that subsided within about 20 minutes, but it literally looked like it sucked all of my impurities out of my pores. I had 75% less blackheads after I used this mask. I was AMAZED. I never thought I would see results like this after just one application. My face felt incredibly smooth, clean, and hydrated. I love this mask, and I will definitely make it one of the staples to my beauty regimen. I definitely recommend to anyone that wants to help their skin.
I was very excited to receive this product in one of their promotional offers in exchange for a honest review.

title: Easily absorbed, may not be the fountain of youth, but feels good on the skin
text: eb5 line has been around for some time now and I have noticed their advertisements in print media over the years, but have not tried any of the line until I received this bottle of Collagen Booster Serum.  I am very surprised that I like this serum as much as I do, and I am more surprised at the competitive pricing for the entire line.  With no added fragrance, my sensitive skin responded well to the light and creamy product that was readily absorbed.  My skin was prepared for moisturizing and there was no irritation or annoyance due to a fragrance of the natural components which can occur.  The pump action is terrific and the cap keeps it protected from the elements, yet it is quick to remove for application.  There is no excessive packaging, so little waste.  Many years ago, Robert Heldfond Jr. and I were casual friends in San Francisco, occasionally having coffee together in North Beach, and I have thought of him each time I would see his father's picture in the advertisements I mentioned earlier.  I very much like to support family businesses and am pleased to finally try the product from his company which now has his wife at the helm.  I look forward to trying other products in the line.

title: Immediate Results...
text:
The wintertime is so drying & my dad hands tend to get such bad dry skin that it cracks, exposing painful lesions all over.
We both started using it the first day it arrived. Much to both of our surprises, it immediately began showing noticeable results on the first application. When I say immediate, I mean right after we applied it our skin was much softer. It wasn't that noticeable on the areas that were already healthy and soft. The areas with cracked or excessively dry skin were immediately transformed into soft and moisturized skin. It feels kind of tingly and minty going on also.
As far as the smell goes, its not noticeable unless you are trying to smell it which I probably wouldn't because what I can smell of it, I didn't really hate it but I definitely wasn't into it either. It's a strange rusted orange color but does not leave stains on anything because it soaks into fabric/clothes just as regular lotion does. The texture is a nice, thick one but considering, it soaks into the skin fairly fast. Actually quicker then most other thick creams used for this purpose.

title: Disappointing
text:
I had high hopes for this body scrub. It‚Äôs priced high so I expected it to be high quality. I was disappointed as soon as I opened it, the product was separated. All of the thick gritty stuff was on one side and all of the liquid oily stuff was on the other side. I had to physically stir it up before I could even use it.

The smell was overpowering. It wasn‚Äôt necessarily bad, just was too strong. I also thought the scrub was way too rough. I used it on my knees and it was border line painful. There is no way I could use this on sensitive skin areas like my stomach or chest. After rinsing off the grit in the bottom of the tub literally hurt my feet stepping on it.

I also do not like how there is no ingredients list on the jar. I like to see what I‚Äôm scrubbing on my skin.

Overall I do not recommend this body scrub.

title: Nice cream, gimmicky packaging
text:
When I opened this package, I had no idea what I was looking at. Inside the Amazon packaging bag was another bag, a plastic bag with a bubble wrap lining and a ziplock type zipper. Inside that, was what looked like a syringe. Honestly, I was at first convinced I had the wrong order as I had no recollection of ordering anything matching what I was seeing. Upon further investigation, I discovered it was the Play Pretend brand of under eye cream. Yes, the Amazon product page does state the the cream comes in a syringe-like tube, and yes, it does state that it comes with a skincare travel bag, this wasn‚Äôt what I had envisioned.
On to the product‚Ä¶
Once I figured out how to open and operate the syringe (hint: remove the large, clear cap, remove the white tip, turn the plunger to unlock) to dispense the under eye cream, I applied some to my face. The scent is strong, like cucumber with an underlying perfume smell. Not unpleasant, but kind of strong for me, someone who is overly sensitive to scents. My problem, I know, and most people will probably really enjoy the scent. The cream is white, smooth, goes on evenly and is absorbed quickly. There is a bit of a cooling sensation which I found pleasant.

The travel bag seems unnecessary to me. It‚Äôs really not much more than a heavy ziplock bag lined with bubble wrap with a large logo reading ‚ÄúSkin Set Go.‚Äù If someone needs a bag, great, but I have several and I don‚Äôt think I‚Äôll be using this one.

According to the company‚Äôs website, Skin Care Go products are made in the USA in small batches. Good. A lot of natural ingredients go into the product, which I like, but the complete list of ingredients from the company‚Äôs website is as follows:

Water (Aqua), Carthamus Tinctorius Seed Oil, Polyacrylate-13, Glycerin, Propylene Glycol, Polyisobutene, Squalane, Sodium Hyaluronate, Acetyl Hexapeptide-8, Cucumis Sativus (Cucumber) Fruit Extract, Retinyl Palmitate, Tocopherol, Palmitoyl Tripeptide-1, Palmitoyl Tetrapeptide-7, Butylene Glycol, Polysorbate 20, Acetyl Octapeptide-3, Caprylyl Glycol, Potassium Sorbate, Phenoxyethanol, Ethylhexylglycerin, Fragrance, Yellow 5 (CI 19140), Blue 1 (CI 42090).

The final verdict:
The product is nice, and while I‚Äôd personally prefer something less heavily scented, I like the way the cream works and what it does for my skin. It‚Äôs very hydrating and brightening, with nothing that irritated my skin. I understand the idea behind the syringe dispenser: it‚Äôs unique, it‚Äôs fun, it‚Äôs memorable. However, there‚Äôs a ton of plastic used that isn‚Äôt necessary, and with the design, I don‚Äôt know how I‚Äôll know when the tube is nearing empty.
Overall, this is a good product, does what it says it does, and if you‚Äôre looking for something a little unusual, give it a try.

title: Moisturizes, Comforts, Some Color Correction-Emphasizes My Pores, Need An Ingredient List
text:
JUNGSAEMMOOL Minifying Cica Mist Balm is a moisturizing balm for sensitive skin that soothes irritation and helps redness. It‚Äôs described as having green calamine to tone down redness and cica pine water to calm skin. But I‚Äôm unable to find a full ingredient list. The box has directions in English but lacks an ingredient list in English, so I don‚Äôt know what‚Äôs even in this product. I have dry, sensitive skin and avoid many skincare ingredients, so I won‚Äôt make this balm or any product part of my daily routine without an ingredient list.

I have used this balm a few times after my moisturizer and before foundation (if wearing makeup). The balm smells light and pleasant, and it adds some comforting moisture. While it tends to sink into my skin, I do get some color correction of redness on my nose and cheeks. But it‚Äôs less than I get with my corrective color makeup. If the balm has healthy ingredients that benefit my skin while also correcting some degree of redness, I‚Äôd likely prefer it to just hiding redness with makeup. But I can‚Äôt judge if the trade off is there without knowing ingredients.

This balm also makes my skin smoother. It feels like it might have silicone and/or glycerin and feels a lot like a primer under my makeup. I like the moist and spreadable texture, except it‚Äôs so soft I can‚Äôt just swipe across the top with the puff for an even amount of product as it smooshes in the balm and gouges out pieces (which I then spread and dab with the puff). It becomes less noticeable as the balm soaks in, but I don‚Äôt like that this settles into and emphasizes pores on my nose. This is just okay for me. 3 stars. Made in Korea.

text:
This Grown Alchemist Anti-Pollution Primer has a gel texture that feels weightless on my skin. This doesn‚Äôt have a lot of ingredients and lacks chemical fragrance, but I find the scent is moderately strong. I assume it‚Äôs mostly from natural lavender, rose and grapefruit oils. I really don‚Äôt love the scent as it smells odd to me, but it mellows out and doesn‚Äôt really bother me. The lavender and grapefruit oils are potential irritants, but my sensitive skin hasn‚Äôt had any visible reaction or real discomfort using this primer.

I have dry skin and when I apply the primer my skin feels a weird initial sensation that reminds me of alcohol, but so far it hasn‚Äôt caused any visible dryness. I do always apply a hydrating essence, serum and cream before the primer and I see the primer has glycerin, so that may be why I don‚Äôt see dryness or maybe something in this just feels mildly irritating to my skin. This does have benzyl alcohol pretty low on the list, so maybe I‚Äôm feeling that but the good part is that I haven‚Äôt had any real issue. I can‚Äôt say if daily use might dry my skin.

This primer is super lightweight, so sheer it‚Äôs invisible and I don‚Äôt feel any sticky residue. It makes my skin feel silky, and my cream and liquid foundations spread smoothly and evenly over it. I do notice a blurring effect, especially around my mouth area where I need all the help I can get. My makeup holds up well all day even though the weather has been so really hot lately. Other than that weird sensation I get that does eventually pass, my skin generally feels comfortable. Like it. 4 stars. Made in Australia.

title: Proven ingredients, but a poor value
text:
I‚Äôm not all that impressed with these products. Neither container lists the ingredients on the label, instead providing the ingredient list on a card that‚Äôs in the box. It shows that the cleaner is a 2% salicylic acid wash, which is a pretty tried and true formulation for treating acne. It is a low-lather, but still effective cleaner, but I didn‚Äôt experience any difference with this compared with other 2% salicylic cleaners that cost far less. It‚Äôs a fine cleaner, but way overpriced for such a tiny (0.51 oz) container.

The repairing night cream is a combination of retinol (0.05%), niacinamide (3%), and hyaluronic acid (2%). All are proven performers, but again, it‚Äôs quite overpriced considering how low of a percentage of retinol is in the formulation. It does a decent job of moisturizing and did not cause any skin irritation. I am a fan of retinol, but the concentration in this cream (0.05%) is well below what I usually use (either 0.1% or 0.5%).

While this product combo is on the right track, the value is just not there considering the amount in the container (one-half an ounce for each). While I would certainly recommend a salicylic acid wash and a retinol-based cream, there are many other options that provide these options at a far lower cost. Four stars for performance; 1 star for value; overall rating of 2.5 stars.
